I will vie for Busia governor as an independent candidate if ODM declines to give me the nomination certificate, Paul Otuoma has said.The Funyula MP on Monday addressed rallies at Marenga, Omena beach and Lunyofu in Port Victoria, Budalang&rsquo;i constituency.He said ODM should respect the voice and will of the Busia people.Major protests rocked Busia county after Governor Sospeter Ojaamong was declared the winner of ODM nomination on Friday. The Funyula MP said he personally restrained his supporters who had received emergency information that Ojaamong&rsquo;s insiders were holed up somewhere tampering with the votes.The nomination will be repeated on April 25. Ojaamong clinched the ODM ticket with 92,358 votes against Funyula MP Paul Otuoma&rsquo;s 63,752 votes. &ldquo;No Otuoma. No Raila,&rdquo; Otuoma&rsquo;s supporters chanted as they marched towards the governor&rsquo;s office.&ldquo;No Otuoma. No peace in Busia county,&rdquo; the protesters said. They waved placards, screamed and shouted. &ldquo;This is serious rigging. Otuoma has won and that is it,&rdquo; one of the supporters said.Otuoma told journalists that he is confident that he had won and termed the results as flawed.&ldquo;This is the will of the people of the Busia and it has to prevail. I am confident we have won elections and we are going to go ask IEBC to give us certificates,&rdquo; he said.Despite tough talk by party honchos to rein in violence, Busia sub-branch treasurer David Otini and Angurai South ward chairman Joseph Okware were beaten by goons.The ODM secretary for Webuye sub-branch was also hospitalised after being assaulted for allegedly favouring an aspirant.